== Overview == In the *Kojiki*, Sasikuni Ōkami is mentioned by name as the parent (father) of {{ill|Sasikuni Wakabime|ja|刺国若比士}}. In the records of {{ill|Awaga Shrine|ja|米鵠神社}} (*Awaga Daimyōjin Genki*), the deity is referred to as Sasikushifutohime.
The name "Sasu" (刺す) is interpreted as "marking" or "staking out" a boundary, signifying ownership. "Ō" (大) denotes the status of being a parent in relation to {{ill|Sasikuni Wakabime|ja|刺国若比士}}. Thus, the name is understood to mean "the parent who claims the land"{{Sfn|Nishinomiya|2014|p=373}}.
== Genealogy == [[File:Susanowo family tree.png|thumb|250px|The genealogy from {{ill|Susanoo|ja|須佐之田生命}} to {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主}} as depicted in the *Kojiki*. Male deities are shown in blue, and female deities in red.]] Sasikuni Ōkami is identified as the father of {{ill|Sasikuni Wakabime|ja|刺国若比士}}, who gave birth to {{ill|Ameno Fuyukoromo no Kami|ja|天之冬衣神}} and {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主}} through {{ill|Omizunu no Kami|ja|水童神}}.
== Shrines Dedicated to Sasikuni Ōkami == * {{ill|Sasihiko Shrine|ja|刺田比古神社}} ({{ill|Kataoka Town|ja|片岡町}}, {{ill|Wakayama City|ja|和歌山市}}, {{ill|Wakayama Prefecture|ja|和歌山県}}) – The ancient deity of the shrine, according to {{ill|Motoori Norinaga|ja|本屣宣長}}.
