{{complex}} {{infobox deity | type = Shinto | children = {{ill|Sashikuni Wakahime|ja|刺国若比売|en:draft||simple|User:Immanuelle/Sashikuni Wakahime}} | father = | consort = | mother = |cult_centre={{ill|Sasadahiko Shrine|ja|刺田比古神社|simple|User:Immanuelle/Sasadahiko Shrine}}|cult_center={{ill|Sasadahiko Shrine|ja|刺田比古神社|simple|User:Immanuelle/Sasadahiko Shrine}}}} {{ill|Sashikuni Ōkami|lt=Sashikuni Ōkami|ja|刺国大神|en:draft|6=simple|7=User:Immanuelle/Sashikuni_Okami|8=fr}} (刺国大神) [[ja:刺国大神]] was a Japanese deity associated with {{ill|Susanoo|lt=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|en}} and the [[Izumo Province|Izumo Province]].<ref name="fountainhead" />{{rp|278}}<ref name=":0" /> [[ja:刺国大神]] He's the father of {{ill|Sashikuni Wakahime|ja|刺国若比売|en:draft||simple|User:Immanuelle/Sashikuni Wakahime}}<ref name="fountainhead">{{cite book |last=Herbert |first=J. |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Sg_JBQAAQBAJ&pg=PT402 |title=Shinto: At the Fountainhead of Japan |publisher=Taylor & Francis |year=2010 |isbn=978-1-136-90376-2 |series=Routledge Library Editions: Japan |page=402 |access-date=2020-qq-21}}</ref>{{rp|278}}<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Sashikuniō • . A History . . of Japan . 日本歴史|url=https://historyofjapan.co.uk/wiki/sashikunio/|access-date=2024-03-22|website=. A History . . of Japan . 日本歴史|language=en-GB}}</ref>.
The Sashikuni in his name refers to land marking.<ref name=":0" /> This makes him analogous to {{ill|Michikaeshi Ōkami|lt=Michikaeshi|en|4=ja|5=道祖神}}
